      <section>                                                           <!--[1-N]-->
        <chapter>                                                         <!--[0-N]-->
          <title>The best negatives</title>                                                          <!--[0-1]-->
          <paragraph>Denmark and Sweden are two states that have a negative interest rate. This rate increase GDP, in fact more interest rate goes down, more GDP raises. Sweden took advantages from negative interest rate, but in this case, immigrants was the very affluence for the state. For the rest of the year, the situation could change. Also Denmark moves down interest rate and it decided to lower again if it will be necessary, because the state took advantages from that financial measure.</paragraph>                                          <!--[0-N]-->
        </chapter>
