          <title>What is deposit rate?</title>								                  <!--[0-1]-->
          <paragraph>It is a rate paid by financial institutions to deposit account holders. Deposit accounts include certificates of deposit, savings accounts and self-directed deposit retirement accounts.</paragraph>                        <!--[0-N]-->
          <paragraph>Hungary and Euro Area have a positive interest rate or near zero, but they have a negative deposit rate. Practically, they do this, because to discourage banks from holding money and thus weaken the currency.</paragraph>
